article.description: Jerron Wilbut scored 15 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer, and CS Northridge beat Cal Poly 76-74 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Wilbut's late 3 lifts CS Northridge over Cal Poly 76-74
article.linkText: Wilbut's late 3 lifts CS Northridge over Cal Poly 76-74
article.story: NORTHRIDGE, Calif. -- Jerron Wilbut scored 15 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer, and CS Northridge beat Cal Poly 76-74 on Thursday night. Cal Poly went up 74-71 with 1:06 to go on Joel Awich's layup. Northridge's Aaron Parks made a pair at the line to get within one, then after an Awich miss, Wilbut grabbed the rebound and eventually drilled a 3-pointer with 18 seconds left to make it 76-74. On Cal Poly's last possession, Reese Morgan missed inside, but grabbed the rebound and kicked it outside but Awich missed a 3 at the horn. CS Northridge (7-12, 2/3 Big West) got 11 points from Zacarry Douglas, while Parks and Tre Hale-Edmerson both added 10. David Nwaba and Brian Bennett led Cal Poly (7-10, 1/3 Big West) with 14 points apiece. Awich finished with nine points. A close game throughout, Cal Poly led 40-39 at intermission.
